<section id="updating-linux" xreflabel="Updateing Device Drivers">
<title>Updating The Device Drivers</title>

<para>
The Rocks ZFS-linux roll comes with a small helper script in
<computeroutput>/opt/zfs/bin/zfs-rebuild-module.sh</computeroutput>.
If your client node runs a different kernel (via updates or other choice),
then running this script will rebuild the zfs modules.
<screen>
# cd /opt/zfs
# ./bin/zfs-rebuild-module.sh
</screen>
</para>
